Define roles and responsibilities: Assign specific roles and responsibilities to each developer to ensure that the project runs smoothly.

Set realistic timelines: Set realistic timelines for each phase of the project and ensure that each developer sticks to their deadlines.

Communicate effectively: Maintain effective communication with the team to ensure that everyone is on the same page and that there are no misunderstandings.

